<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="594" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[113,1089,815,1128]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,224,815,839]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">Remarks.</emphasis>
This specimen differs from the African 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[651,788,816,839]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bequaerti">
<emphasis box="[651,673,816,839]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[686,788,816,839]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">bequaerti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only by the non-transparent elytra without lighter whitish coloration in their posterior half.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="594" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[113,1089,815,1128]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,260,879,903]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">Distribution.</emphasis>
Three 
<taxonomicName box="[335,560,879,903]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[335,476,880,903]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">Macrosiagon</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[576,726,880,903]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipunctata">
<emphasis box="[576,598,880,903]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[612,726,880,903]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">bipunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[740,888,880,903]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis box="[740,762,880,903]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[775,888,880,903]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Laporte" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[940,1080,880,903]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="terminata">
<emphasis box="[940,962,880,903]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[976,1080,880,903]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">terminata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are widespread in the Afrotropical Region and go through the southern part of the Arabian Peninsula to the Indian subcontinent or even further to the east and west. All three species show slight morphological or color variability in different areas (probably because of different ecological conditions). One can conclude that the Afrotropical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[796,935,1008,1031]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bequaerti">
<emphasis box="[796,818,1008,1031]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[833,935,1008,1031]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">bequaerti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may have the same 
<typeStatus box="[174,220,1040,1064]" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">type</typeStatus>
of distribution, but there is no record of this species from the Arabian Peninsula so far. Such a disjunct distribution may indicate that the Indian specimen belongs possibly to a new species sister to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[338,476,1104,1127]" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bequaerti">
<emphasis box="[338,360,1104,1127]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[374,476,1104,1127]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="594">bequaerti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. More material is necessary to make a sound decision.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
